    {
      "id": "a6b2cc58c505e5376b63cdfd76d582dd8983c781",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2015-11-17 15:24:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI tried this on my test nodes (I am affected by this problem too greatly) and it does not help completely.\nSure, I might be hitting the problems on 5th iteration of the test instead of the 1st-2nd one now, but that's about it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b95088c7da2e291393a6a766bed1b59d3755ce86",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2015-11-17 22:45:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOleg, if the test (do you mean only sanity/test_60a ?) is being run in a loop, I presume I need also to flush/sync after the last step of LLOG_TEST_RECNUM cancels in llog_test_10(), and why not also at the beginning of llog_test_10() before the first LLOG_TEST_RECNUM records are being created ?\nBTW, do the new OOM occurrences you trigger still occur at the same point, ie during the \"10c: write 131072 more log records\" step?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "24fb175564e2c6253bf991ad5023591e0db3c94e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2015-11-18 14:10:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nfor me the crash mostly happens after test 7, e.g.\n <4>[47404.850166] Lustre: 5616:0:(llog_test.c:1079:llog_test_7()) 7g: test llog_gen_rec\n\nor\n [27989.459883] Lustre: 5366:0:(llog_test.c:1068:llog_test_7()) 7f: test llog_changelog_user_rec\n [27990.736301] Lustre: 5366:0:(llog_test.c:962:llog_test_7_sub()) 7_sub: records are not aligned, written 64452 from 64767\n [28007.152686] rpcbind invoked oom-killer: gfp_mask=0x200da, order=0, oom_adj=0, oom_score_adj=0\n\n\nBy running in a loop I mean not just test 60a, but the whole sanity + sanityn one after another in a loop.\nAnd granted it used to fail on first iteration on one of my nodes very frequently. Now it holds longer.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
