        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2015-11-19 15:31:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOleg, I presume that before running with this patch your runs were failing/OOM in llog_test_10() right? \nDid you have some time to analyze one of the OOM/crash on your test box? If yes, did you find the same situation I have described in LU-7329 where the memory has been filled by the slabs allocated for the arrays of keys that are waiting to be freed by the huge backlog of journal commit callbacks?\nAlso, I can give a try to add 2 more sync()s at start+end of llog_test_10() in this patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
