        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2015-11-19 22:45:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOleg, do you use a smaller memory-sized VM or a real node with \"small\" memory ? May be we should add more sync()s in all llog_test_...() routines to also regularly flush journal commit callbacks ? Or we may face some sort of other leak ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0bca430accff5fe8a4a70119d8cc7c3bb9766991",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2015-11-20 13:09:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nit's a VM that has 3G RAM, this is more than what we have in autotest, but in my case I also have whole set (ie mds, osts) on the same node with standard sized disk in /tmp (that is tmpfs).\n\nI typically run this test out of build tree as\n\nwhile :; do rm -rf /tmp/* ; SLOW=yes REFORMAT=yes sh sanity.sh ; sh llmountcleanup.sh ; rm -rf /tmp/* ; SLOW=yes REFORMAT=yes sh sanityn.sh ; sh llmountcleanup.sh ;done",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
